cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on image colorization, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method also involves the use of neural networks to learn object semantics and generate color distributions, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on two datasets, PASCAL VOC2012 and COCO-stuff, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) research.
